+{"id":"frankenpandas-expr01","priority":2,"status":"closed","closed_at":"2026-04-28T23:30:00Z","closed_by":"cc_1","resolution":"fix(fp-expr): escape sequences + decimal validation","title":"[BUG] fp-expr parser lacks escape sequence support and malformed float detection","comment":"Multi-pass audit found: (1) String literals didn't support backslash escapes (\\n, \\t, \\r, \\\\, \\', \\\"); pandas eval/query strings like \"O\\'Brien\" would fail. (2) Multiple decimal points (1.2.3) weren't caught until parse::<f64>() failed. Fixed both + added 6 tests. Commit: 985fe07"}
+{"id":"frankenpandas-fuzz01","priority":2,"status":"closed","closed_at":"2026-04-29T00:05:00Z","closed_by":"cc_1","resolution":"test(fuzz): 12 join_series edge-case seeds","title":"[FUZZ] join_series corpus needs edge case coverage","comment":"Extended join_series fuzz corpus from 5 to 17 seeds. Coverage: empty series, duplicate labels, all-null values, null propagation, large overlap, disjoint labels, asymmetric cardinalities, cross product, mixed dtypes, single elements. Also found harness issue: NaN-containing JoinedSeries comparison uses == causing false drift detection (workaround: use Null instead of NaN in seeds). Commit: 06ab9fb"}
+{"id":"frankenpandas-hll01","priority":2,"status":"closed","closed_at":"2026-04-29T00:20:00Z","closed_by":"cc_1","resolution":"fix(fp-groupby): HyperLogLog integer overflow","title":"[BUG] HyperLogLog::estimate() integer overflow on high rho values","comment":"HLL registers can store rho values up to 64 (from leading_zeros()), but estimate() used 2_u32.pow(r) which overflows when r > 31 (panic in debug, wrap in release → incorrect cardinality estimates). Fixed by using 2_f64.powi(). Added test for high rho values. All 66 fp-groupby tests pass. Commit: 2497512"}
